<br>
I believe I can claim credit for that fix, heh. I pestered Verant for months with emails and feedbacks saying that instead of deleting no rent items when people camp or LD, they could just let no rent items stay on the character file and then run the check when people log on...use the last timestamp from anywhere on the character file to determine if the person has been offline for more than 10,20,30 min. If yes, delete all no rent items. If not, let them keep the no rent items. It looks like they did exactly that, no?<br>
<br>
I believe I am also the father of /guildmotd. The implementation was shortly after I suggested it, the name of the command was coined by me, the dual use of the command both to write the message and to read it was also me, the wording of the announcement of the new functionality was almost identical to my suggestion. The only thing they added was the name of the officer who put up the message, that I hadn't thought of. <p><CENTER>
